# Ops Docs and Changelog

## Reading
1. Start with `ops/CURRENT.md` for the active snapshot.
2. Open only the single task file relevant to your current work.
3. Do not read completed tasks or old change logs unless explicitly asked.

## Writing
- When starting a task: move its file from `ops/tasks/backlog/` to `ops/tasks/in-progress/`.
- When finishing a task: move its file to `ops/tasks/done/` and append a summary line to `ops/CURRENT.md`.
- Append change entries to the current month file in `ops/changes/YYYY-MM/`.
- Keep entries concise: one line per change, prefixed with the date and agent role.

## Task File Format
```
# TASK-NNN: Short title
Owner: <role>
Status: backlog | in-progress | done
Created: YYYY-MM-DD
---
Acceptance criteria (bullet list).
```

## Architecture Decisions
- Record significant choices in `ops/decisions/ADR-NNN.md`.
- Format: Title, Context, Decision, Consequences.
